Package: xtop
Version: 0.43.1-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl
Installed-Size: 23600
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 v0.43.1 introduces lean daemon mode: when started with --fleet-hub the
 agent now uses a 9-collector essentials-only set, caps history ring at
 30 snapshots (down from 600), and runs a 5-minute memory-relief loop
 that returns idle pages to the OS. Eliminates the multi-GB RSS growth
 seen on long-running container hosts. Override with XTOP_DAEMON_RICH=1
 to restore the legacy rich-collector behavior.
